TITLE: Global audience demand for streaming Asian movies, series grows with hits like 'Squid Game'
SUMMARY: Viewership for Asian TV content is growing on streaming services in the U.S., following popular hits like "Squid Game" and "Everything Everywhere All At Once."

TITLE: Now Boarding: Why airlines are turning to bigger planes to beat airport congestion
SUMMARY: On this episode of "Now Boarding," CNBC discusses how airlines are turning to bigger planes as airport congestion and a pilot shortage limit new flights.

TITLE: White House and Republicans reach a tentative deal to avoid U.S. default
SUMMARY: House Republicans have reached a tentative deal with the White House to address the nation's debt ceiling and avoid a default.

TITLE: Turkey votes in runoff election after candidates double down on nationalism and fear
SUMMARY: Country analysts are all but certain of an Erdogan victory.

TITLE: The tech trade is back, driven by A.I. craze and prospect of a less aggressive Fed
SUMMARY: The Nasdaq closed out its fifth straight weekly gain and is again outperforming other U.S. indexes as tech stocks are back in favor.

TITLE: The No. 1 'underrated' city in the world, according to 175 travel experts: It's the 'new hot city'
SUMMARY: New York, Paris and Tokyo may be on your travel bucket list, but there are plenty of cities that don't get enough credit and are well worth a visit. This year's pick, according to travel experts, is Bologna, Italy.

TITLE: Consumers are starting to fire up China's pandemic-battered economy, two ETF experts find
SUMMARY: A bullish economic trend may be underway in China after a challenging reopening.

TITLE: JPMorgan Chase cut about 500 jobs this week, including technology and operations roles
SUMMARY: Like many financial firms, JPMorgan periodically trims staff during the year, even as it hires thousands more workers to fill roles.

TITLE: Marvell shares rocket 32% on earnings beat and 'tremendous' business potential for A.I.
SUMMARY: Shares of Marvell Technology surged about 32% off the back of quarterly earnings results.

TITLE: Inflation rose 0.4% in April and 4.7% from a year ago, according to key gauge for the Fed
SUMMARY: The core personal consumption expenditures price index was expected to increase 0.3% in April, according to a Dow Jones estimate.

TITLE: German economy enters recession as first-quarter GDP data is revised lower
SUMMARY: The German economy entered a technical recession in the first quarter of this year, after posting a contraction of 0.3% over the three-month period.

TITLE: OpenAI's Sam Altman reverses threat to cease European operations
SUMMARY: OpenAI's CEO threatened to cease operations in Europe if regulation expanded, then seemed to reverse his stance saying there are "no plans to leave."

TITLE: Tech layoffs ravage the teams that fight online misinformation and hate speech
SUMMARY: Meta, Amazon, Alphabet and Twitter have all drastically reduced the size of their teams focused on trust and safety as the companies cut costs.

TITLE: Fintech firm Klarna halves net loss in first quarter as it races toward profitability
SUMMARY: The results show that Klarna is making "significant strides" toward profitability on a monthly basis by the second half of 2023, the firm said.

TITLE: French riot police fire tear gas at climate protesters outside TotalEnergies shareholder meeting
SUMMARY: French police on Friday fired tear gas at climate activists who tried to prevent the annual general meeting of oil giant TotalEnergies.

TITLE: China's gambling hub opens $2 billion resort with a giant copy of London's Big Ben
SUMMARY: Macao — often referred to as the Las Vegas of Asia — has added yet another luxury casino resort to the Cotai Strip. And this time it's a British-themed one.

TITLE: TikTok Shop, a rising threat to Shopee and Lazada in Southeast Asia
SUMMARY: TikTok Shop poses a threat to e-commerce players such as Shopee and Lazada in Southeast Asia as it pushes aggressively into the region.

TITLE: This Singaporean couple runs a side business preserving dead animals — and it’s bringing in 5 figures a month
SUMMARY: "Serving animals, whether alive or the dead, is very meaningful to me ... Through taxidermy, I help [pet owners] with their grieving," said Vivian Tham.

TITLE: China's travel recovery gets more attention, but India's outbound market is 'booming' even faster
SUMMARY: India's outbound travel market is growing much faster than any other outbound market in the world, according to Agoda's CEO, Omri Morgenshtern.

TITLE: Nvidia nears elite trillion-dollar market cap club of Apple, Microsoft, Alphabet and Amazon
SUMMARY: The surge in Nvidia following its explosive sales guidance could help catapult the stock into the group of public companies with a $1 trillion market cap.

TITLE: Call to ‘Buy Japan’ is premature, say Bank of America analysts
SUMMARY: Strategists say the approach to buy Japanese stocks as well as the yen — could be one for next year, not this year.

TITLE: Elon Musk's brain implant company Neuralink announces FDA approval of in-human clinical study
SUMMARY: The implant, which Neuralink calls the "Link," aims to help patients with severe paralysis control external technologies using only neural signals.

TITLE: Nvidia shares surge to record close with 24% rally
SUMMARY: Nvidia shares are on track to beat the company's 2021 all-time high closing price after it significantly beat estimates, driven in part by an AI frenzy.

TITLE: Ford CEO Jim Farley says Chinese automakers such as BYD are its greatest EV rivals
SUMMARY: Ford CEO Jim Farley used Warren Buffett-backed BYD as the prime example of a Chinese automaker that has successfully developed and sold electric vehicles.

TITLE: JPMorgan is developing a ChatGPT-like A.I. service that gives investment advice
SUMMARY: Banks including Goldman Sachs and Morgan Stanley are testing A.I. internally, but JPMorgan may be the first to release a GPT-like product directly to customers.

TITLE: Chinese augmented reality glasses maker Nreal rebrands as Xreal as it takes on tech giants
SUMMARY: Chinese augmented reality glasses maker Nreal rebranded to Xreal — a name it hopes will encapsulate its expansion into Europe and latest products.

TITLE: Chinese state-sponsored hackers infiltrated U.S. naval infrastructure, secretary of the Navy says
SUMMARY: The U.S. Navy was "impacted" by Chinese state-backed hackers, which targeted infrastructure in the U.S. and Guam in an attack first flagged by Microsoft.

TITLE: Amazon's air cargo head changes jobs, will now oversee workplace-safety unit
SUMMARY: Sarah Rhoads, who joined Amazon in 2011, has become one of Amazon's top logistics executives and helped to rapidly expand its air-cargo arm.

TITLE: How the A.I. explosion could save the market and maybe the economy
SUMMARY: Whether it's personalized shopping or self-driving cars, AI will become a factor in virtually everyone's lives.

TITLE: A.I. cryptocurrencies jump after Nvidia reports booming artificial intelligence demand
SUMMARY: AI-themed cryptocurrencies got a lift Thursday from excitement around Nvidia and its increasing demand for chips that power AI applications.
